column2: Sunny- clear- breezy.  Warm.  Quiet in terms of birds.  No eagles today.
Sunny- breezy.  Heron on lake shore.
Partly sunny- mild.  Couple of fishermen out.  Dead raccoon under boat!
Bald eagle circling.  Another perched.  Screeching some.  Sunny- light breeze.  Jet skier on lake.  Much less milfoil than normal.
Clear and very warm (about 60 F).  Few fishermen in small boats.  Light breeze.  Beautiful.
90% cloud cover no wind.  Difficult to navigate through all of milfoil- possibly variable leaf milfoil.
Max depth found was 7'.  Lots of milfoil/coontail- extremely dificult to navigate.  Winds out of ESE at 15 mph.  Integrated sample 0-2m- 200mls filtered for chla.  Hydrolab quanta used for profile.

North winds at 10-15 mph.  Integrated smaple 0-2m.  Difficult to maintain position due to wind.  Pulled up a large amount of coontail with the anchor.  Difficult to tell if secchi hit bottom due to coontail and drift.
Windy and cold.  Lots of coontail on anchor.  100% cloud cover- beautiful day for December!
Dock is under water- most of lake has milfoil topping out.  Landing is in disrepair and needs attention.  wind 5-8 mph.
Cloudy- calm and hot.  Lots of EWM- coontail and elodea.  Site depth was 11ft.
Bad storm from Point to GB.  Had to wait the storm out at the boat landing for nearly 2 hours.

column1: Bottom 1.5 - 2 feet of sampling site covered in solid coontail and elodea

column2: Secchi disk disappeared in aquatic plants at 5'.  Entire lake bottom is covered with coontail- elodea and EWM.
Entire lake is covered with aquatic plants (EWM- Coontail- Elodea).  Secchi was lost in plants so an accurate measurement was tough to obtain.
Solid aquatic plants on the whole lake.  Bottom two profile data sets were in among aquatic plants.
Entire lake is solid aquatic plants. Coontail- EWM- Elodea.
D.O. meter malfunctioned.  No D.O. readings were reliable
Abundant plants throughout lake.  Profile at 2 m was taken among dense vegetation.
Dense vegetation at sampling site.  At 2 meters down in the profile the YSI probe was among dense plants.
Secchi disk hit dense vegetation before it was out of sight.  Also 2 meters down in the profile YSI probe was among dense vegetation.
Plants cover the bottom of the lake. Secchi and YSI probe both hit plants
secchi disk and YSI probe hit plants before hitting the bottom
